# Cub3d Project Roadmap

## Week 1: Project Setup and Understanding

### Day 1: Project Setup 
-[x] Create project repository
-[x] Set up development environment
-[x] Install necessary libraries (MinilibX)
-[x] Study the project requirements thoroughly
-[x] Set up a basic Makefile

### Day 2-3: Theory and Research
-[x]Learn raycasting principles
-[x]Study the math behind 3D rendering
-[x]Research Wolfenstein 3D rendering techniques
-[x]Create diagrams for understanding raycasting concepts
-[x]Make notes on vector math required for the project

### Day 4-5: Basic Structure
-[ ]Design the program architecture
-[x] Create essential data structures
-[x] Implement basic window management with MinilibX
-[x] Set up main program loop
-[x] Plan the file parsing approach

## Week 2: Map Parsing and Basic Display

### Day 6-7: Map Parsing
-[x] Define map file format (.cub)
-[x] Implement map file parser
-[x] Handle texture path and color definitions
-[x] Create data structures to represent the map grid
-[x] Add error handling for invalid maps

### Day 8-9: Basic 2D Rendering
-[x] Display the parsed map as a 2D grid
-[x] Implement a simple top-down view
-[x] Add player position representation
-[x] Test various map configurations
-[x] Implement basic validation of map boundaries

### Day 10: Player Setup
-[x] Define player data structure
-[x] Handle initial player position and orientation
-[x] Implement basic input handling for movement
-[x] Add collision detection with walls

## Week 3: Raycasting Implementation

### Day 11-13: Basic Raycasting
-[x] Implement the bresenham algorithm
-[x]Calculate wall distances using raycasting
-[x]Determine wall heights based on distance
-[x]Create a basic 3D view with solid-colored walls
-[x]Implement field of view calculations

### Day 14-15: Texture Loading
-[ ]Load wall textures from files
-[ ]Implement texture mapping basics
-[ ]Calculate texture coordinates
-[ ]Apply textures to walls
-[ ]Handle different wall directions with different textures

## Week 4: Enhancing the Rendering

### Day 16-17: Improved Texturing
-[ ]Add ceiling and floor colors
-[ ]Implement texture coordinate precision
-[x]Fix fisheye effect
-[ ]Add proper wall shading based on distance
-[ ]Implement texture selection based on wall orientation

### Day 18-19: Player Movement
-[x] Refine player movement controls
-[x]Add rotation with arrow keys or mouse
-[x]Implement smooth movement and collision detection
-[x]Implement strafing (sideways movement)
-[ ]Add acceleration and deceleration for realistic movement

### Day 20: Performance Optimization
-[ ]Optimize raycasting algorithm
-[ ]Implement view distance limitations
-[ ]Add frame rate management
-[ ]Profile and identify bottlenecks
-[ ]Implement rendering optimizations

## Week 6: Polishing and Finalization

Testing and Debugging
-[ ]Perform comprehensive testing on different maps
-[ ]Fix rendering bugs
-[ ]Resolve memory leaks
-[ ]Test performance on different systems
-[ ]Fix any remaining issues with textures or movement
